- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a new alignment mechanism for text-dependent speaker verification, which involves processing and analyzing natural language. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new differentiable neural network alignment mechanism for text-dependent speaker verification, which involves training a neural network to produce a supervector representation of an utterance. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing): The paper involves processing speech signals to extract features for text-dependent speaker verification. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach for text-dependent speaker verification using neural networks and alignment models.
